UID:20261105-TheSchaghenletterrecordsthepurchaseofMan@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260714T170654Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20261105
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20261106
SUMMARY:The Schaghen letter records the 'purchase' of Manhattan — 400th a
 nniversary
DESCRIPTION:A letter by Dutch official Pieter Schaghen\, dated Nov. 5\, 1
 626\, reported that colonists had 'purchased' the island of Manhattan fr
 om its Native inhabitants for goods worth 60 guilders. It is the only co
 ntemporary document of the transaction.\n\nhttps://www.newnetherlandinst
 itute.org/history-and-heritage/additional-resources/dutch-treats/peter-s
 chaghen-letter/
URL:https://www.newnetherlandinstitute.org/history-and-heritage/additiona
 l-resources/dutch-treats/peter-schaghen-letter/
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
