DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270714
SUMMARY:The blackout that broke the city's spirit — 50th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:Lightning strikes knocked out power for some 25 hours\, unlea
 shing widespread looting and arson across the crime-plagued\, cash-strap
 ped city.\n\nhttps://www.britannica.com/event/New-York-City-blackout-of-
 1977
URL:https://www.britannica.com/event/New-York-City-blackout-of-1977
CATEGORIES:anniversary
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:20270728-SilentParademarchesdownFifthAvenue110tha@nyc-calendar
DTSTAMP:20260714T170654Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270728
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270729
SUMMARY:Silent Parade marches down Fifth Avenue — 110th anniversary
DESCRIPTION:Thousands of Black New Yorkers marched in silence down Fifth 
 Avenue to protest lynchings and the East St. Louis massacre.\n\nhttps://
